#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.sign:39
msgid "The sign of `x`. This is a scalar if `x` is a scalar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.sign:51
msgid ":obj:`signbit`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.sign:53
msgid ":obj:`copysign`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.sign:57
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.sign:58
msgid ""
"There is more than one definition of sign in common use for complex "
"numbers.  The definition used here, :math:`x/|x|`, is the more common and "
"useful one, but is different from the one used in numpy prior to version "
"2.0, :math:`x/\\sqrt{x*x}`, which is equivalent to ``sign(x.real) + 0j if x."
"real != 0 else sign(x.imag) + 0j``."
msgstr ""

